    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "that's a pretty strong take. but what about the people in manufacturing towns that have been gutted by all this? isn't it kind of unfair to just say \"deal with it\" when those industries are being wiped out by cheap imports? isn't there a valid argument that protecting those jobs is more important than a few cents extra on groceries?",
