      "content": "While it is true that manufacturing towns suffer from trade deficits, the solution isn't to protect inefficient industries with tariffs that hurt everyone else. The real problem is that those specific jobs were lost due to a lack of investment in modernization and education, not just because of foreign competition. Instead of raising prices for all Americans, the government should focus on retraining workers and subsidizing domestic innovation to make our industries competitive again.",
